				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song of the Sirens timing question<a name="43961"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 3 04 1:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The simple way to understand it is this: you cannot cast charm on a mob that is already charmed.  You can only charm hostile creatures and a charmed mob is not hostile.
<br />

<br />
It may actually break early - 3 ticks is optimum and not guaranteed.  You can try to time it so that your song lands the instant charm breaks, but the simple fact is, until charm breaks, you cannot land another charm on the mob.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
