				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song of the Sirens timing question<a name="44147"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 4 04 10:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually Steppy, if you try to cast charm song(I remember this specifically for song of sirens) on your pet before it breaks, it will stop you less than a second into your cast and say you have an invalid target. But if you leave the song running it will not break. In other words, you can't time it since the game wont let you start casting before Song of Sirens breaks.
<br />

<br />
If you just left the song of sirens running(this is the only charm song that lets you do this BTW so don't get too cozy with the idea) it will try to refresh every tick, thus, if your pet breaks between ticks it will be very angry at you until your song ticks again(provided the pet didn't interrupt you) and he will have a fresh change of heart.
<br />

<br />
So to answer your question, if all your singing is song of the sirens and you don't stop singing it through the full duration, the pet will not break for more than 1 tick, in fact its very likely the pet will be re-charmed in a few seconds after it breaks. Resist check is made whenever a song is sung on a valid target so a resist check will be made when song of sirens is reapplied on your target.
<br />

<br />
If you stop singing song of the sirens after charming, you will need to re-sing it after charm breaks, but the game won't let you do it before, so even then, the pet should not break for more than 1 tick. It does not automatically break for more than 1 tick, songs only take 3 secs to cast so whenever it gets sung you will get a resist check and it will apply if you succeed.
<br />

<br />
ehh, repeated myself over and over there, hope its not too confusing...<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
