				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song of the Sirens timing question<a name="44939"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 8 04 10:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Statistically speaking it hardly makes a difference whether you leave the song running or not. If you leave it running it will refresh every 6 seconds, so the auto-recharm will happen anywhere between 0 and 6 seconds after a charm-break. With a randomly timed charm-break this willl on average result in a recharm after 3 seconds.
<br />

<br />
If you start the song by hand after a charmbreak it takes 3 seconds to cast, same as the average recharm-time. The only difference is the time it takes to press a key in reaction to the break-message<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
So, not too much of a difference, but starting it by hand gives you a fixed time for charm to re-apply (or resist<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />) that you can count on. 
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
